data.title: 15 fun facts about Demi Moore on her birthday
data.meta_description: Learn more about actress Demi Moore as we look at her background, romantic life, career and more.
data.text:
From her years as a member of the 'Brat Pack' to her climb to the top of the Hollywood mountain, Demi Moore is one of the most well-known actresses of her generation.

As she celebrates her 54th birthday today, we take a few minutes to look at some interesting points along her timeline including her career highlights, romantic interests and her giant doll collection.

15 things you might not have known about Demi Moore

By Mike Rose, cleveland.com

November 11, 2016

Next slide: An alien encounter

(Photo: Associated Press)

Is that a weather balloon?

Demi Moore was born in Roswell, New Mexico on November 11, 1962. Roswell is best known for its links to purported alien encounters and conspiracies galore.

(Photo: Associated Press)

Would you be my neighbor?

After moving to California and marrying musician Freddy Moore, Demi found herself inspired to become an actress thanks to one of her neighbors, actress Nastassja Kinski.

(Photo: Associated Press)

Her leading men

During her career, Moore has been involved with Emilio Estevez, Bruce Willis and Ashton Kutcher. She was engaged to Estevez and was married to Willis. She and Kutcher married in 2005 but are now divorced.

(Photos: Associated Press)

Is there a doctor in the house?

Don't be a Brat

Moore was part of the ‘Brat Pack,’ a group of young actors who rose to prominence in the 1980s. Other members included Emilio Estevez, Ally Sheedy, Rob Lowe and Judd Nelson.

(Photos: Associated Press)

That's my girl

Moore’s daughter, Rumer Willis, has become a star in her own right, both as an actress and musician.

(Photo: Associated Press)

Table for four

Moore joined then husband Bruce Willis, Sylvester Stallone and Arnold Schwarzenegger as investors in the Planet Hollywood chain.

(Photo: Associated Press)

Yeah, baby!

Moore was also an executive producer on all 3 ’Austin Powers’ films.

(Photo: Associated Press)

Unchained at the box office

According to BoxOfficeMojo, Moore's highest grossing film is 'Ghost' which brought in more than a half-billion dollars globally.

(Photos: Associated Press)

Show me the money

Moore set a then record $12.5 million payout for an actress for her role in ’Striptease’

(Photo: Columbia/Castle Rock)

Hit or miss

Moore was one of three finalists for the lead role in ‘Flashdance’ that she eventually lost to Jennifer Beals.

Sandra Bullock took over the lead in ‘While You Were Sleeping’ after Moore backed out.

(Photos: Associated Press)

Going for gold

Moore has been nominated for numerous awards during her career including a Primetime Emmy, two Golden Globes and a SAG award. She has twice won a People’s Choice Award.

(Photos: Associated Press)

That's a stinker

RottenTomatoes ranks 1991's 'Nothing but Trouble' as her lowest-rated film. The movie also featured Dan Aykroyd, Chevy Chase and John Candy.

Fashion flash

Moore was once the face of Versace.

(Photo: Associated Press)

You're never too old

The New York Times reports Moore owns a collection of more than 2,000 dolls.

(Photo: Associated Press)

Photo: Associated Press

What's next?

Demi is set to appear in in 'Love Sonia'

Photos: Associated Press
